 rgaret
CREATED:20251208T193656Z
DESCRIPTION:Duke University Libraries will be turning the pages of the Bir
 ds of America on the first Friday of every month! We welcome you to stop 
 by and watch-what bird will be next?\n\nBirds of America is one of the gr
 eatest undertakings in the history of both art and ornithology. Almost 20
 0 years after its publication\, it remains a primary resource for scienti
 sts and scholars. This four-volume\, double-elephant-folio edition on han
 dmade paper measures three feet tall and two feet wide and comprises 435 
 hand-colored prints impressed from copperplate engravings. Of the origina
 l 175 to 200 complete sets\, 125 have survived. Nine species of those dep
 icted have since gone extinct.
DURATION:PT30M
DTSTAMP:20260204T201213Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260306T121500
LAST-MODIFIED:20260204T201213Z
