CREATED:20260302T195208Z
DESCRIPTION:The Manhattan Chamber Players bring together accomplished solo
 ists and ensemble musicians\, combining their talents in a flexible line-
 up that brings fresh vitality to chamber music. Their diverse instrumenta
 tion allows for adventurous programming and dynamic performances.\n\nThey
  present a duo of piano quintets here\, each inhabiting vastly different 
 musical worlds but sharing an emotional weight. Though separated by nearl
 y a century\, Brahms and Weinberg both turn to the form of the piano quin
 tet as a means of wrestling with grandiose emotions and narrative\, creat
 ing a powerful dialogue across time.\n\nBrahms's Piano Quintet is a corne
 rstone of Romantic chamber music\, refined and elegant in its approach. '
 What inner strength\, what richness\,' wrote Clara Schumann of the quinte
 t's early drafts. In stark opposition\, Weinberg's Piano Quintet evokes a
  dark psychological landscape\, shaped by the trauma of the Second World 
 War\, offering reflections on suffering and resilience.\n\nProgram\nBrahm
 s: Piano Quintet\, in F minor\, Opus 34\nMieczslaw Weinberg: Piano Quinte
 t\, Opus 18
DURATION:PT2H
